"```sql\nSELECT COUNT(*)\nFROM client\nWHERE gender = 'M'\nAND district_id = (\n    SELECT district_id\n    FROM district\n    ORDER BY A15 DESC\n    LIMIT 1 OFFSET 1\n);\n```\n\nThis SQL query counts the number of male clients (`gender = 'M'`) in the district where the second-highest number of crimes were committed in 1995. The subquery orders the districts by the number of crimes in 1995 (`A15`) in descending order and selects the district with the second-highest number of crimes using `LIMIT 1 OFFSET 1`."